# When to use it vs the Spark DataFrame API

## The performance rule of thumb

- **Fast** — maps to a **single** Spark op (`filter`, `groupBy`, `join`, `withColumn`) → same plan, no penalty
- **Slow** — a **per-row Python callback** (no type hint) or a **driver materialization** → pay for it

## The guidance

- **pandas-on-Spark** — scale an existing pandas codebase / a pandas-fluent team
- **native DataFrame API** — new pipelines, full feature set, avoid driver collects & per-row callbacks
- Flip for free: **`pandas_api()` ↔ `to_spark()`** — never all-or-nothing

**One engine, wearing whichever surface fits the job.**
